This paper deals with the problem of quantifying similarity between relations in knowledge bases, which is a core problem in natural language processing and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a method based on the divergence between conditional probability distributions over entity pairs, which is a common approach in machine learning and information retrieval. The paper also uses a simple neural network to parameterize these distributions, which is a common technique in deep learning. Overall, the paper combines ideas from several sub-fields of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB).
